The paper deals with lower bounds for oblivious data structures, which are a type of data structure designed for situations where data needs to be stored at an untrusted server. This topic is closely related to computer security (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of oblivious RAM (ORAM), which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper presents lower bounds for various classic data structures, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC).
